# Docs Formatting

Apply these formatting rules when editing markdown documentation.

## Article titles

- Use sentence case: capitalize only the first word, proper nouns, product names, and acronyms.
- Task/guide articles use a bare imperative verb: "Add custom CSS", "Design your menu", "Install a review app".
- Reference articles (sections, settings, blocks) use a noun phrase: "Cart drawer", "Product badges", "Typography".
- Never use gerunds ("-ing" form) as the opening verb: "Using custom CSS" and "Adding tag filtering" are non-conforming.

## Headings

- Keep exactly one H1 (`#`) at the top of the page.
- Preserve the page's existing heading hierarchy unless it is clearly invalid.
- Keep heading labels consistent and concise.
- Ensure one empty line appears above each heading (except the first H1).

## Lists and sentence quality

- Use one bullet style consistently within the page.
- Ensure sentences are complete and end with proper punctuation.

## Tables

- Keep settings documentation in readable tables.
- Use markdown tables by default.
- Use HTML tables only when the page already depends on HTML table markup.